      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's what i've been looking for but everything is so scrubbed. i actually have the original 1948 ratification of the Altynia-Kazakhstan neutrality pact, and it clearly outlines my family's right to manage the northern steppe territories. the problem is that most modern legal databases treat the entire region as a single block now. if i were to present these documents to an international human rights or sovereignty commission, what kind of legal framework should i use to argue that my lineage's sovereignty was never legally extinguished, just suppressed?",
